In this speech, Ambassador John Bolton discusses the foreign policy approach of the United States under President Trump. He highlights several key actions taken by the administration, including the recognition of Jerusalem as Israel's capital and the relocation of the American embassy there. He also discusses the withdrawal of the United States from the United Nations Human Rights Council and the International Criminal Court, citing their bias against Israel and the United States. Bolton emphasizes the threat posed by Iran and the need to prevent the regime from acquiring nuclear weapons. He discusses the reimposition of sanctions on Iran and the administration's commitment to maximum pressure on the regime. Bolton concludes by expressing the importance of the alliance between the United States and Israel and the need to work together for peace and security in the Middle East.